{{Orphan|date=May 2014}}
{{Italic title}}
'''''A British Picture''''' ({{ISBN|978-1-904915-32-4}}, 2008) is the autobiography of the English [[film director]] [[Ken Russell]]. Its title was changed to '''''Altered States''''' in the United States.

When the author [[Tony Fletcher]] requested an interview with Russell as reference for his biography of the [[The Who|Who]] drummer, [[Keith Moon]], Russell replied that he had already said everything he wanted to say about Moon in ''A British Picture''. The book at no point mentions Moon.<ref name="Dear Boy: The Life of Keith Moon">{{cite book|last=Fletcher|first=Tony|authorlink=Tony Fletcher|title=Dear Boy: The Life of Keith Moon|publisher=Omnibus Press'|year=2005}}</ref>

