{{EngvarB|date=September 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox book <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = My Name Is Mina | image = My Name Is Mina.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = | author = [[David Almond]] | illustrator = | country = England | language = English | genre =[[Children's fiction]] | published = 2010 ([[Hodder & Stoughton|Hodder Children's Books]]) | media_type = Print (hardback) | pages = 300 | isbn = 9780340997260 | oclc = 765619939 }}
'''''My Name Is Mina''''' is a 2010 children's novel by [[David Almond]]. It is a prequel to ''[[Skellig]]'' and is about Mina, a [[homeschooled]] girl who lives across the road from the house that Michael's family moves into at the beginning of ''Skellig''. The novel takes the form of a stream of consciousness journal.
==Reception== ''[[Booklist]]'', in a starred review of ''My Name Is Mina'', wrote "Almond is rather brave to have written a prequel to Skellig (1998), a book that was the essence of originality. So many things could have gone wrong. But he is too shrewd—and fine—a writer to let that happen"<ref name=wccls/>; and ''[[Kirkus Reviews]]'' found it "A fascinating, if breathless ramble through the cosmos."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/david-almond/my-name-mina/ |title=My Name Is Mina |date=24 August 2011 |website=Kirkus Reviews |publisher=Kirkus Media LLC |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>
The ''[[School Library Journal]]'' wrote "Almond portrays Mina as a girl with a great love of words and learning, and he plays joyfully with language. This might make for tricky going for some readers, but it is truly a wonderful book.";<ref name=wccls/> and ''[[Voice of Youth Advocates|VOYA]]'' called it "a lyrical, whimsical novel".<ref name=wccls/> A ''[[The Guardian|Guardian]]'' reviewer wrote that it is "a wonderful book in its own right" and "joyous."<ref>{{cite news |last=Sedgwick |first=Marcus |date=4 September 2010 |title=My Name Is Mina by David Almond |url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2010/sep/04/my-name-is-mina-david-almond |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>
''My Name Is Mina'' has also been reviewed by ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-385-74073-9 |title=My Name Is Mina |date=15 August 2011 |website=Publishers Weekly |publisher=PWxyz LLC|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''Library Media Connection'' magazine,<ref name=wccls/> ''[[The Horn Book Magazine|The Horn Book]]'',<ref name=wccls>{{cite web |url=https://catalog.wccls.org/Mobile/BakerAndTaylor/Review?ISBN=9780385740739&UPC=9780385740739(hardcover)&position=2 |title=My Name Is Mina |website=catalog.wccls.org |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[English Association|The Use of English]]'' magazine,<ref>{{cite journal |date=January 2012 |title=My Name Is Mina |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/78347700/my-name-mina-by-david-almond |journal=The Use of English |publisher=The English Association |volume=63 |issue=3 |page=263 |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[Bookmarks (magazine)|Bookmarks]]'',<ref>{{cite journal |date=January 2012 |title=My Name Is Mina |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/70046273/my-name-mina |journal=Bookmarks |publisher=Jon Phillips |issue=56 |page=46 |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[Children's Book Council of Australia|Reading Time]]'',<ref>{{cite journal |date=May 2011 |title=My Name is Mina |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/61220122/my-name-mina |journal=Reading Time |publisher=Children's Book Council of Australia |volume=55 |issue=2 |page=30 |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[School Librarian]]''.<ref>{{cite journal |date=December 2010 |title=My Name is Mina |author=Peter Hollindale |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/57276924/my-name-mina |journal=School Librarian |publisher=School Library Association |volume=58 |issue=4 |page=228 |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[BookTrust]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.booktrust.org.uk/a/books/view/30741 |title=My Name is Mina: The prequel to Skellig |publisher=booktrust.org.uk |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''The Deakin Review of Children's Literature'',<ref>{{cite journal |year=2013 |title=My Name is Mina by D. Almond |url=https://ejournals.library.ualberta.ca/index.php/deakinreview/article/view/20036 |journal=The Deakin Review of Children's Literature |publisher=University of Alberta |volume=3 |issue=1 |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref>{{cite news |last=Paul |first=Pamela |date=14 October 2011 |title=Bookshelf: Night Children's Books |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/16/books/review/bookshelf-night.html |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> and the ''[[National Post]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Marchand |first=Philip |date=16 December 2011 |title=Open Book: My Name is Mina, by David Almond |url=http://news.nationalpost.com/afterword/open-book-my-name-is-mina-by-david-almond |newspaper=National Post |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>
It was shortlisted for the 2012 [[Carnegie Medal (literary award)#Shortlists|Carnegie Medal]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Clements |first=Toby |date=27 March 2012 |title=Patrick Ness's A Monster Calls leads Carnegie and Kate Greenaway medal shortlists |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/9169695/Patrick-Nesss-A-Monster-Calls-leads-Carnegie-and-Kate-Greenaway-medal-shortlists.html |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> and the 2011 [[Guardian Children's Fiction Prize#Longlists and shortlists|Guardian Children's Fiction Prize]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Eccleshare |first=Julia |date=1 October 2011 |title=Guardian children's fiction prize: the shortlist |url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/sep/30/guardian-childrens-fiction-prize-shortlist |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>
